<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/340589-spoiler-so-i-guess-she-got-caught-in">SPOILER

So I guess she got caught in the end?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_340589'><a id="like_count_community_question_340589" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/340589?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">3 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F21936809-the-kind-worth-killing">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/340589-spoiler-so-i-guess-she-got-caught-in">7 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/340589-spoiler-so-i-guess-she-got-caught-in">See all 8 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/16156980-jacqueline"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1358928324i/16156980._UX100_CR0,2,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/16156980-jacqueline">Jacqueline</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I found the ending to be the perfect conclusion to a captivating story. It 's hard for me to believe that there are no more twists, and I can easily i<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I found the ending to be the perfect conclusion to a captivating story. It 's hard for me to believe that there are no more twists, and I can easily imagine that the father has already come to the rescue, or that somehow they bulldoze over the bodies instead of uncovering them. I love that I walk away from the novel with the same conflicing emotions that I had throughout - Lily is a murderer, and in theory I do not want her to get away with it, but in my heart I keep rooting for her (I would like her to stop finding "the kind worth killing", though). The conclusion allows me to continue to enjoy this debate with myself. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
