<div id="review_3212884558" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3212884558" />
    <a title="Ahmad Sharabiani" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/614778-ahmad-sharabiani"><img alt="Ahmad Sharabiani" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1194930432p2/614778.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3212884558?book_show_action=true">Mar 01, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ahmad Sharabiani" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ahmad Sharabiani" href="/user/show/614778-ahmad-sharabiani">Ahmad Sharabiani</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780062450319" href="/book/show/25944394-the-kind-worth-killing">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/614778-ahmad-sharabiani?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/614778-ahmad-sharabiani?shelf=crime-mystery">crime-mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/614778-ahmad-sharabiani?shelf=united-states">united-states</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/614778-ahmad-sharabiani?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/614778-ahmad-sharabiani?shelf=21th-century">21th-century</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3212884558" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13575325406026250780">The Kind Worth Killing, Peter Swanson<br/><br/>In a tantalizing set-up reminiscent of Patricia Highsmith’s classic Strangers on a Train… <br/><br/>On a night flight from London to Boston, Ted Severson meets the stunning and mysterious Lily Kintner. Sharing one too many martinis, the strangers begin to play a game of truth, revealing very intimate details about themselves. <br/><br/>Ted talks about his marriage that’s going stale and his wife Miranda, who he’s sure is cheating on him. Ted and his wife were a mismatch from the</span>
  <span id="freeText13575325406026250780" style="display:none">The Kind Worth Killing, Peter Swanson<br /><br />In a tantalizing set-up reminiscent of Patricia Highsmith’s classic Strangers on a Train… <br /><br />On a night flight from London to Boston, Ted Severson meets the stunning and mysterious Lily Kintner. Sharing one too many martinis, the strangers begin to play a game of truth, revealing very intimate details about themselves. <br /><br />Ted talks about his marriage that’s going stale and his wife Miranda, who he’s sure is cheating on him. Ted and his wife were a mismatch from the start—he the rich businessman, she the artistic free spirit—a contrast that once inflamed their passion, but has now become a cliche.<br /><br />But their game turns a little darker when Ted jokes that he could kill Miranda for what she’s done. Lily, without missing a beat, says calmly, “I’d like to help.” After all, some people are the kind worth killing, like a lying, stinking, cheating spouse. . . .<br /><br />Back in Boston, Ted and Lily’s twisted bond grows stronger as they begin to plot Miranda's demise. But there are a few things about Lily’s past that she hasn’t shared with Ted, namely her experience in the art and craft of murder, a journey that began in her very precocious youth.<br /><br />Suddenly these co-conspirators are embroiled in a chilling game of cat-and-mouse, one they both cannot survive . . . with a shrewd and very determined detective on their tail.<br /><br />تاریخ خوانش روز چهاردهم ماه اکتبر سال 2018 میلادی<br /><br />عنوان نوعی کشتن؛ نویسنده: پیتر سوانسون؛<br /><br />در یک پرواز شبانه از «لندن» به «بوستون»، «تد سیورسون» با «لیلی کینتنر» خیره کننده و مرموز دیدار میکند؛ تد در مورد ازدواج خود و همسرش «میراندا» سخن میگوید، و ...؛ <br /><br />تاریخ بهنگام رسانی 31/04/1399هجری خورشیدی؛ ا. شربیانی</span>
  <a data-text-id="13575325406026250780" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


